1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:05,200
Today you all have gathered here

2
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:09,640
to do the Guru Puja.

3
00:00:14,720 --> 00:00:19,080
Your Guru is a Mother first and then a Guru

4
00:00:20,480 --> 00:00:24,320
and that has given Me a greater help.

5
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:31,720
We have had before also many Guru Pujas,

6
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:35,480
mostly in England.

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:38,520
And you should wonder why

8
00:00:38,720 --> 00:00:44,520
Mother always somehow is doing Guru Puja in London.

9
00:00:45,240 --> 00:00:50,000
The time falls in such a way that it is in Guru Puja,

10
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:56,040
I am here, during that time I have to be in London.

11
00:00:57,240 --> 00:01:03,960
So many years we have been doing Guru Puja in England.

12
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:15,280
All things happen if according to ritambhara pragya

13
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:17,400
then there must be some reason

14
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:23,480
why Mother is here in England for a Guru Puja.

15
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:31,800
It is stated in the Puranas that

16
00:01:32,040 --> 00:01:37,440
the Adi Guru Datattreya

17
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:41,800
worshipped Mother

18
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:47,800
along the banks of the river Tamasa.

19
00:01:48,840 --> 00:01:53,200
Tamasa is the same as your Thames

20
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:58,800
and He himself came and worshipped here.

21
00:02:00,800 --> 00:02:05,120
And the druids, those who had

22
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:11,080
the manifestation of the Stonehenge and all that,

23
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:17,560
are originated from that time in this great country of Shiva,

24
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:21,560
of the Spirit.

25
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:30,440
So the Spirit resides here as in the heart of human beings,

26
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:35,240
and the Sahasrara

27
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:42,360
is in the Himalayas where Sadashiva exists at the Kailasha.

28
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:47,240
This is the great secret

29
00:02:47,440 --> 00:02:52,960
of we having so many Guru Pujas here.

30
00:02:55,200 --> 00:03:00,240
To culminate it today and to this special type of Guru Puja

31
00:03:00,600 --> 00:03:04,400
in the year of the sixtieth birthday of your Mother

32
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:09,840
is, has a special, very, very special significance

33
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:12,280
because is the Guru Sashti -

34
00:03:12,480 --> 00:03:18,360
is the sixty years of your Guru has been celebrated today.

35
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:24,720
And that's how it's a very big occasion that you all have gathered

36
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:29,200
under the influence of again ritambhara pragya.

37
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:40,640
So all that has happened has happened by the nature's own gift to you

38
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:43,520
and everything has worked out so well

39
00:03:43,720 --> 00:03:48,040
because that was the desire of the Divine

40
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:51,280
and the design of the Divine.

41
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:55,920
So the river Thames, which we call Her as Thames -

42
00:03:56,120 --> 00:04:00,240
you see, English have a method of making everything English.

43
00:04:00,920 --> 00:04:04,800
Like Bombay they made it - Mumbai was Bombay,

44
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:09,200
you see, like Calcutta, like all other words just like that.

45
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:13,120
Like Varanasi was made into Benares,

46
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:19,000
River Thames which was really Tamsa was called as Thames.

47
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,520
Now from the name Tamsa one should know

48
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:28,600
that is a place of Tamo Guna.

49
00:04:29,080 --> 00:04:33,440
Is a place where left-sided resided since long.

50
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:39,120
So people were very worshipful, left-sided people, emotional type,

51
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:41,360
and they worshipped God more

52
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:45,360
than that they went into yagyas and all that.

53
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:50,080
And Datattreya lived here

54
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:55,960
and meditated on the banks of River Thames.

55
00:04:56,320 --> 00:05:00,960
That's why Guru puja here has to give us a great background

56
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:07,120
for your awakening of the Guru Principle.

57
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:10,880
We have to go to the roots of everything

58
00:05:11,080 --> 00:05:13,920
so that we understand the importance of it.

59
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:18,320
Unless and until you know the roots and the traditions behind

60
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:21,720
you cannot understand the depth,

61
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:27,520
the gravity, the intensity of any puja.

62
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:33,000
Today we have gathered here to do the Guru Puja, again.

63
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:37,160
The reason is we have got a Guru Principle within ourselves

64
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:39,160
as I told you last time

65
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:41,200
and also I have given elaborately

66
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:46,560
the Ten Commandments as expressed within us

67
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:50,040
which are describing the different

68
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:54,360
the different types of essences within us.

69
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:06,320
The essence of Guru Puja has to be awakened within us.

70
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:12,400
That's how we are having this program here.

71
00:06:17,760 --> 00:06:21,640
Now it is important

72
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:27,960
that we have to establish

73
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:31,240
the dharma within us.

74
00:06:31,640 --> 00:06:35,840
Without the dharma you cannot have the ascent.

75
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:41,920
And as I have told you before that the cleanliness

76
00:06:42,280 --> 00:06:46,080
of your being

77
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:51,240
depends on how much dharma you follow, religiously.

78
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:55,200
At the time of Moses

79
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:59,520
it was worked out

80
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:04,280
and all the rules and regulations

81
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:08,800
were created for realized souls.

82
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:12,400
But as I read in one of the books - it was very good,

83
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:15,280
because if I had said this, people would not have believed -

84
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:21,120
that it had to be changed.

85
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:25,560
I think during the speech the children should not be here,

86
00:07:25,840 --> 00:07:27,480
it's better to take them out.

87
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:30,520
After the speech you can bring them along - those who make noises.

88
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:31,800
Those who are quiet it's all right,

89
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:35,160
but those who are making noises you better bring them out.

90
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:38,520
If they are going to make noises, better to be out or near the door

91
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,080
so that if they make noises you can get out,

92
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:42,560
so there is no disturbance.

93
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:45,840
And during the puja is all right, you could be at the gate,

94
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:49,520
door or some place from where you can go.

95
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:56,520
So the laws and regulations that were given to human beings

96
00:07:56,800 --> 00:08:00,560
were actually for the realized souls who would understand.

97
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:06,720
But when Moses must have discovered the way human beings are,

98
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:13,000
He must have changed them to very strict rules,

99
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:15,920
because with human beings as they are,

100
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:18,480
one has to be extremely strict.

101
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:21,320
They can't understand anything but fear.

102
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:24,200
If you have

103
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:28,680
a stick in your hand, you can put them right.

104
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:32,320
Without that stick human beings won't listen.

105
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:36,240
They are only all right if there's a fear.

106
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,360
Now if you see

107
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:42,920
the today condition of all the nations,

108
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:48,800
those who are having leaders, or prime ministers, or presidents

109
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:54,200
they are all people extremely strict,

110
00:08:54,880 --> 00:09:00,840
very dominating and very dry.

111
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:05,640
And normally people like such people.

112
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:09,160
Even Hitler succeeded because of that nature.

113
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:13,040
So the character of a guru so far

114
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:16,240
has been of a very strict nature

115
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:19,760
for people who are not realized.

116
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:24,120
Normally a guru doesn't - a good guru, Satguru,

117
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:28,320
He doesn't like to talk to people much.

118
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:30,640
They throw stones

119
00:09:30,840 --> 00:09:34,440
or they don't like to talk to people

120
00:09:34,640 --> 00:09:39,960
who are not realized.

121
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:45,520
But if they are realized then these Gurus change their attitude

122
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:49,320
towards the people who want to see them.

123
00:09:49,680 --> 00:09:51,240
There is a tremendous difference

124
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:54,680
between a person who is a realized and non-realized

125
00:09:54,880 --> 00:09:58,160
in the protocol of God.

126
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:02,520
A man may be the king or anything, he'll be asked to sit outside.

127
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:05,880
It has nothing to do with what position you enjoy.

128
00:10:06,160 --> 00:10:10,320
As long as he is a realized soul and not possessed

129
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:12,080
he is given the highest position.

130
00:10:12,280 --> 00:10:15,040
But if you are possessed then also the Guru will tell him

131
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:16,560
that "You get out from here,

132
00:10:16,760 --> 00:10:19,760
first get rid of your possession and then come."

133
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:22,840
And all these strict rules were there,

134
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:25,720
that such and such person must be killed,

135
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:29,320
such and such person must be given a punishment

136
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:31,720
of cutting the hands, cutting the feet,

137
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:37,160
even absolutely destroying the eyes.

138
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:41,040
This was done because they were not realized souls.

139
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:44,240
It was the great realization of Moses, I think,

140
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:49,240
that He took to another kind of law which is known as Sharia now

141
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,520
and that's what the Muslims are following.

142
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,440
In a way it's good I think,

143
00:10:53,640 --> 00:10:58,960
because people who are now normal people really deserve such a rule,

144
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:02,400
but it should not be so fanatical that you cannot discriminate

145
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:06,400
between a realized soul and a non-realized soul.

146
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:12,000
Now the Guru within you

147
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:15,400
will be awakened if you are strict with yourself.

148
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:18,600
That's one point is very important.

149
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:22,200
Unless and until you are strict with yourself

150
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:24,960
the Guru will not be awakened within you.

151
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:29,560
People who are lazy lumps, who cannot sacrifice anything,

152
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:34,880
who are very fond of comfort can never be gurus, take it from Me.

153
00:11:35,280 --> 00:11:37,920
They can be good administrators, they can be anything,

154
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:40,560
but never a guru.

155
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:45,160
A guru should be willing to live the way he has to live.

156
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:48,240
He should be able to sleep on stones,

157
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:52,280
he should be able to sleep under any circumstances.

158
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:55,840
Not that the disciple should force on him,

159
00:11:56,160 --> 00:12:00,160
but it should be his own nature, that he can adjust himself.

160
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,280
Comfort cannot crawl on a guru.

161
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:07,760
Now those who want your Guru Principle to be awakened

162
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:11,160
must know that you should not ask for comfort.

163
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:14,680
Even for a thing like that, yesterday you saw the dancing,

164
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:17,480
one has to do real tapasya.

165
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:19,720
Intensive tapasya you have to do,

166
00:12:19,920 --> 00:12:24,520
you cannot learn even a thing like dancing

167
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:28,720
without going into a penance about it.

168
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:34,000
So a guru has to go through all penances is important.

169
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:39,200
Sahaja Yogi need not go, but a guru Sahaja Yogi has to do it.

170
00:12:39,560 --> 00:12:41,520
We have to have penances,

171
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:45,960
and the penance can be any kind of desire you have.

172
00:12:46,160 --> 00:12:48,560
Say, supposing you are very fond of food,

173
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:53,600
just don't eat the food that you want to eat.

174
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:56,200
If you are very fond of sweet food,

175
00:12:56,480 --> 00:13:01,360
then eat something very bitter, raised to power hundred and eight.

176
00:13:02,160 --> 00:13:08,040
And if you are fond of some sort of a very ...

177
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:11,000
- as Indians are, sometimes -

178
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:16,480
... very spicy food then eat so bland the food, without salt.

179
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:19,200
Teach your tongue to behave itself.

180
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:23,640
It doesn't behoove a guru to put his attention to food.

181
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:27,720
I have seen some of the Sahaja Yogis, they are all right

182
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:30,400
when the food is there, quite concentrated,

183
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:34,080
but when it comes to the programme they have no concentration.

184
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:39,520
Such a sad thing, such people cannot be gurus. They can be cooks, good,

185
00:13:42,520 --> 00:13:46,440
or could be food-tasters or something like that.

186
00:13:46,760 --> 00:13:50,000
Will suit them better, but if they have to be gurus

187
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:54,720
they must learn to control their tongue and their desires.

188
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:59,520
I mean, fasting is a good thing for such people, fasting is very good.

189
00:13:59,720 --> 00:14:02,280
All the time they are worried, what are we going to have for lunch,

190
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:04,280
what are we going to have for dinner?

191
00:14:04,480 --> 00:14:08,520
Such people cannot have their Guru Principle awakened,

192
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:13,000
neither they can be gurus. So please be careful.

193
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:17,080
The guru must have control over the tongue.

194
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:20,360
He must know when to get angry

195
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:24,040
and when to be gentle.

196
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:29,760
He must know what to say when,

197
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,680
how much to say.

198
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:38,560
That's why many gurus have been more effective by not speaking.

199
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:43,480
Silence is the best way you can help others,

200
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:47,520
but when it comes to explaining Sahaja Yoga, you should speak.

201
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:50,680
But I have seen with some people they are very eloquent

202
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:53,120
when it comes to nonsensical things,

203
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:55,280
but when it comes to Sahaja Yoga, they don't know anything

204
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:57,000
about Sahaja Yoga.

205
00:14:57,200 --> 00:14:58,800
So you have to be the master of Sahaja Yoga,

206
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:00,600
if you have to be a Guru,

207
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:04,360
not only in talking, but in your behaviour, in everything.

208
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:09,400
And the karamat

209
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:11,680
is the ...

210
00:15:11,920 --> 00:15:15,280
I don't know if you use charismatic-word, charismatic they call it

211
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:19,240
or you say, the one how to do it

212
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:23,320
how to raise the Kundalini, how to put it at the Sahasrara,

213
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:27,720
how to break the Sahasrara, all these things you must know,

214
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:32,600
how to spend your knowledge is viniyoga in Sanskrit.

215
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:37,560
Guru principle is awakened in a person

216
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:39,840
when he himself has achieved something.

217
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:44,240
Imagine a half-baked guru going along talking as a Guru.

218
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:48,960
He'll end up as a disciple ultimately.

219
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:51,880
So you have to be master of your own,

220
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:54,440
but when the Guru Principle comes in

221
00:15:54,640 --> 00:15:56,440
you have to give it to others,

222
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:59,560
it's a question of giving it to others.

223
00:15:59,760 --> 00:16:04,280
So you have to be at a higher level to give it to others,

224
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:07,960
have to be at a very high level.

225
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:10,520
If you are attached to money, if you are attached to food,

226
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:15,160
if you are attached to mundane things of life, you cannot give.

227
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:22,520
Now the higher state than that can be achieved,

228
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:27,160
which is naturally in Me, but can be achieved,

229
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:33,320
is that you don't have to have any dependence like that,

230
00:16:33,680 --> 00:16:36,840
that any rules and regulations,

231
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:41,520
like saying that I will have no worry about food,

232
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,440
I should fast, this, that -

233
00:16:43,640 --> 00:16:49,360
it all ends up. When you eat but don't eat,

234
00:16:50,560 --> 00:16:53,600
that's the state one should have,

235
00:16:53,840 --> 00:16:57,320
that you are eating the food

236
00:16:57,760 --> 00:17:01,720
and if you ask, "Did you have your lunch?"

237
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:04,720
"I don't know ..."

238
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:08,080
"Will you have your lunch?"

239
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:10,880
"I don't know ..."

240
00:17:11,120 --> 00:17:17,080
Absolutely indifferent to the problems of the body.

241
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:20,120
"Where did you sleep?"

242
00:17:20,320 --> 00:17:23,240
"I don't know ..."

243
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:27,600
"What did you eat, what will you have?"

244
00:17:27,840 --> 00:17:30,480
"I don't know ..."

245
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:35,240
This kind of a state is called ateeta state where you go beyond

246
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:40,440
and whatever you do, you are doing it

247
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:44,360
because it is to be done. Without paying any attention to it,

248
00:17:44,680 --> 00:17:46,960
is automatic.

249
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:51,760
Nothing is important, but this is -

250
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:55,160
before becoming ateeta you have to steady yourself,

251
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:57,360
"Nothing is important," you see, is a, avir bhava

252
00:17:57,560 --> 00:18:01,920
they call it, is a kind of a drama you have to put in.

253
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:05,000
"Oh, nothing is important, this carpet is not important,

254
00:18:05,200 --> 00:18:07,840
I should try to sleep on the cement."

255
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:10,520
First you have to do that.

256
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:13,400
But after some time it happens

257
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:16,240
that you don't remember whether you slept on the cement

258
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:20,520
or on a cot, "Where did I sleep? I don't know."

259
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:23,920
That is the ateeta state.

260
00:18:26,680 --> 00:18:32,240
And that state is to be achieved now by many Sahaja Yogis-

261
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:35,680
in a state where you go beyond.

262
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:40,440
Say there is somebody who is before you and you have to get angry.

263
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:43,960
All right, you give them left, right, left, right nicely

264
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:47,960
and then you are smiling next moment.

265
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:52,840
Did you get angry with that person? "I don't know, did I?"

266
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:59,600
Like Buddha once said something

267
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:03,000
in one village

268
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:05,000
and there was a horrible fellow who got up

269
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:07,880
and said lots of things to him.

270
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,640
And when He went to the next village the fellow felt

271
00:19:10,840 --> 00:19:14,680
that "Oh, I should not have done that," Left Vishuddi, perhaps.

272
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:17,960
So he went down and said, "I am sorry Sir, I have said so

273
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:19,720
and I should not have said it,

274
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:21,480
I didn't know You are the enlightened one,

275
00:19:21,680 --> 00:19:23,200
so it happened, so forgive me."

276
00:19:23,400 --> 00:19:26,120
He said "When, where did you say?"

277
00:19:26,880 --> 00:19:28,080
He said, "In the last village."

278
00:19:28,280 --> 00:19:30,520
"Oh, everything in the last village I have left there alone

279
00:19:30,720 --> 00:19:33,560
I don't take with me."

280
00:19:34,560 --> 00:19:37,320
That is the ateeta state that you have to reach.

281
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:42,080
So even not to feel, it's not important.

282
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:46,760
These identifications when they drop out completely

283
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:52,720
then you are doing things in akarma state,

284
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:58,320
where, like sun is shining it doesn't know it is shining.

285
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:01,600
When the vibrations are flowing you don't know it is flowing.

286
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:04,160
Already it has started working in you.

287
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:06,720
You are surprised, you raise the hands and the Kundalini is rising.

288
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:09,920
You don't know you are raising the Kundalini actually.

289
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:12,760
How do you raise it?

290
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:16,160
You don't know, that's it.

291
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:21,280
That state has already started ateeta in you,

292
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:24,120
but get it established in every walk of life,

293
00:20:24,320 --> 00:20:29,000
everything, that you go beyond.

294
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:34,040
And if you can manage that,

295
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:38,240
that's the highest that you have to reach.

296
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:47,880
Now with the incarnations it's very different,

297
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:50,120
it's the other way round.

298
00:20:50,320 --> 00:20:52,760
Everything is the other way round.

299
00:20:52,960 --> 00:20:56,880
They don't have to do any tapasya.

300
00:20:57,960 --> 00:21:01,440
They don't have to starve, they don't have to cleanse themselves,

301
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:06,400
whatever they do is the punya.

302
00:21:06,920 --> 00:21:09,040
They don't have to collect punyas either.

303
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:12,880
If they kill somebody it is dharma.

304
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,240
If they hit somebody it is the dharma.

305
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:18,960
Nothing they do wrong.

306
00:21:19,280 --> 00:21:22,160
They are absolutely immaculate.

307
00:21:22,640 --> 00:21:25,680
If they deceive someone, they cheat someone,

308
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:28,200
it's perfectly all right.

309
00:21:28,440 --> 00:21:34,000
Because for a higher goal you have to give up the smaller goals.

310
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:38,080
It's justified in our day-to-day life you'll see,

311
00:21:38,360 --> 00:21:40,880
that when you are defending your country,

312
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:44,200
there is an enemy on you, if you have to defend your country

313
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,800
you can slay him.

314
00:21:47,160 --> 00:21:51,760
You can cheat him, diplomatically you can befool him.

315
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:53,600
Is allowed, why?

316
00:21:53,800 --> 00:21:58,040
Because for a higher goal you have to give up the smaller goal.

317
00:21:58,240 --> 00:22:00,800
But for an incarnation it is always the higher goal.

318
00:22:01,080 --> 00:22:04,200
He is not bothered about smaller goals at all.

319
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:06,960
He doesn't have to weigh, think, rationalize

320
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:11,600
or to train himself or do some drama or anything, it's all done.

321
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:16,440
Even the movement, every movement, every movement of an incarnation

322
00:22:16,720 --> 00:22:20,640
has a ripple in it, which is for the good.

323
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:24,880
There is nothing, not even a moment is such

324
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:29,560
which is not for the good of the world.

325
00:22:29,920 --> 00:22:33,160
So the incarnation is a very different thing,

326
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:37,560
that is not to be achieved, that has to be.

327
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:41,800
Now for example

328
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:45,960
the incarnation is the bhokta, is the enjoyer,

329
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:48,080
He is the enjoyer of everything.

330
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,240
Many people, say, have created,

331
00:22:50,440 --> 00:22:53,120
now we have a carpet here from Turkey.

332
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:56,000
These carpets were created by Turkish peoples

333
00:22:56,240 --> 00:23:00,240
some time back for an incarnation to sit.

334
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:03,400
So the ritambhara pragya will bring it round in such a way

335
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:07,160
that at least I see it,

336
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,920
or I have it,

337
00:23:10,280 --> 00:23:12,720
so that their souls will be blessed,

338
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:16,440
so that they feel nice.

339
00:23:17,280 --> 00:23:22,120
Like Michelangelo has made that not for popes, I can tell you.

340
00:23:23,920 --> 00:23:27,560
and not for all the rubbish people who go there.

341
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:30,240
Neither Blake did all that work

342
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:35,080
for the useless people who want to go and see nude artists.

343
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:40,280
It was all done for the incarnation to see.

344
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:44,440
That's the way they have blessed the most,

345
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:48,640
because they are beyond, nothing touches them, nothing is important,

346
00:23:48,840 --> 00:23:51,560
but it's not rational or anything that they have trained themselves,

347
00:23:51,760 --> 00:23:55,560
but it is automatically they have.

348
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:02,960
Like Shri Krishna had to marry sixteen thousand women.

349
00:24:03,200 --> 00:24:04,320
Can you imagine?

350
00:24:04,560 --> 00:24:09,800
In those days of monogamy he would be prosecuted hundred times.

351
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:14,160
The reason was he has sixteen thousand powers

352
00:24:14,520 --> 00:24:15,920
and He was to be born

353
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:20,480
with those sixteen thousand powers on this Earth

354
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:27,120
and five elements became His queens.

355
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:36,120
He had to do some justification to have them around.

356
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:43,880
And as I have now Sahaja Yogis whom I have,

357
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:46,960
I mean, given Realization.

358
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:51,360
So automatically I am your Mother, is established.

359
00:24:51,720 --> 00:24:53,400
But for Him there was no way out

360
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:57,320
but to marry His sixteen thousand powers.

361
00:24:57,680 --> 00:25:00,640
And so He married, but He was never married,

362
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:04,720
He was a bachelor out and out all His life.

363
00:25:05,080 --> 00:25:08,840
Because He is Yogeshwara and He is a brahmacharya.

364
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:14,520
Who can marry ... Him?

365
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:22,800
So for Them all these worldly things are just a drama,

366
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:26,040
has no meaning at all.

367
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,640
It's just a drama.

368
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:32,040
A person

369
00:25:33,440 --> 00:25:39,320
who is not an incarnation should not try to be.

370
00:25:40,560 --> 00:25:45,880
That's not the right of a human being.

371
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:48,560
Like a policeman standing on the road,

372
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:52,120
if he puts his hands right, left - we follow it.

373
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:57,640
But you ask some mad man to go and stand there, he will be arrested.

374
00:26:01,520 --> 00:26:05,400
So for normal people, even you are a guru

375
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:09,280
you shouldn't allow them to touch your feet.

376
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:14,320
Only an incarnation's feet must be touched

377
00:26:15,520 --> 00:26:18,040
and nobody else's feet must be touched.

378
00:26:18,480 --> 00:26:20,040
Of course in samayachara

379
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:23,320
like as we have in India the custom to touch the feet of the father,

380
00:26:23,600 --> 00:26:27,480
but because the father is a representative of the father

381
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:30,960
in you, that's why - or the mother.

382
00:26:32,440 --> 00:26:34,160
But that's symbolic,

383
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:37,840
but in reality you are not to surrender yourself to anybody else,

384
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:40,200
but to an incarnation.

385
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:43,160
Also if there's a teacher in your,

386
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:47,400
any art or in anyway the master, you must touch his feet.

387
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:50,760
Even to take his name you have to pull your ears.

388
00:26:51,160 --> 00:26:54,520
But nobody

389
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:58,880
who is a human being should make touch your feet,

390
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:02,640
especially the Sahaja Yogis should not.

391
00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:08,120
Nobody should ask anyone to touch your feet.

392
00:27:08,440 --> 00:27:10,280
As an elder you may,

393
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:14,760
that's a different point, but not as a guru.

394
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:17,240
Is a very dangerous thing,

395
00:27:17,440 --> 00:27:20,280
once you start it, you know what it happens, with so many,

396
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:23,800
they have just gone out of Sahaja Yoga.

397
00:27:24,360 --> 00:27:27,560
So to develop the Guru Principle within you

398
00:27:27,800 --> 00:27:32,680
first of all you must develop yourself, fully.

399
00:27:32,880 --> 00:27:37,400
Now how to develop yourself a Guru Principle, one must see.

400
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:44,880
We have got the ten principles within you, as I told you before

401
00:27:45,320 --> 00:27:48,680
and we should develop these all ten principles in such a way,

402
00:27:48,920 --> 00:27:52,560
that we stand out from others.

403
00:27:53,320 --> 00:27:56,840
Yesterday as I told you that when we do dhyana-dharana-samadhi

404
00:27:57,120 --> 00:28:00,560
and achieve the blessings of the ritambhara pragya,

405
00:28:00,840 --> 00:28:05,280
then put that whole thing

406
00:28:05,480 --> 00:28:08,880
onto different areas

407
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:13,040
as called as desh or bhoomi.

408
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:17,360
How you spend them is the point - is through mantras,

409
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:20,240
cleanse it through mantras,

410
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:23,800
cleanse it through your attention,

411
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:29,040
every day you must know which chakra to be cleared out.

412
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:31,880
You must know about yourself, where is the problem,

413
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:33,760
how it is to be cleansed,

414
00:28:34,040 --> 00:28:35,880
how we have to clear it out.

415
00:28:36,160 --> 00:28:38,320
Do not take it for granted.

416
00:28:38,600 --> 00:28:41,880
Many people who have got, say, left-sided problem,

417
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:44,080
you will just bring them lemon and chillis

418
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:47,080
and think that Mother has done the job.

419
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:52,000
I can only do the job temporarily,

420
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:56,400
but if there is a vacuum again you will suck in.

421
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:58,280
You see ...

422
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:03,520
these vacuums within you feel hungry again to have some more.

423
00:29:03,960 --> 00:29:06,240
So to take out that vacuum is your job

424
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:08,960
and for that you have to religiously get

425
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:12,640
after all your defects.

426
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:15,840
That's the most important thing for all of you.

427
00:29:16,120 --> 00:29:21,720
And try to put full attention to all these different deshas

428
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:25,080
- is the nations, they are called like this.

429
00:29:25,440 --> 00:29:27,960
And once you have cleared it,

430
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:32,160
it is enlightened, is full of light,

431
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:34,640
then you call it pradesh,

432
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:38,840
means the desha has been enlightened.

433
00:29:40,640 --> 00:29:41,680
Once that has achieved

434
00:29:41,880 --> 00:29:45,840
then you have reached the point you can become a guru,

435
00:29:46,120 --> 00:29:48,840
but still you are not a Satguru.

436
00:29:49,120 --> 00:29:55,080
To become the Satguru you must achieve the state of ateeta.

437
00:29:56,280 --> 00:29:57,960
The ateeta state is such

438
00:29:58,200 --> 00:30:04,120
that the person who is not a good man will tremble before you.

439
00:30:05,600 --> 00:30:07,640
A man who is a liar,

440
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:12,080
who has cheated others will lose his tongue.

441
00:30:14,080 --> 00:30:17,600
A man who has adulterous eyes,

442
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:24,960
who is a man without, no control,

443
00:30:25,280 --> 00:30:28,320
without any control over his mind

444
00:30:28,600 --> 00:30:32,360
as far as the women are concerned or men are concerned,

445
00:30:32,640 --> 00:30:36,000
such a person will have shaking in his eyes.

446
00:30:36,280 --> 00:30:38,040
Some of them will shake,

447
00:30:38,280 --> 00:30:42,560
those who have been possessed will be shaking with it.

448
00:30:42,840 --> 00:30:46,960
They'll be all exposed before the light of a Sat Guru.

449
00:30:47,200 --> 00:30:50,560
When you achieve that you don't have to fight them,

450
00:30:50,840 --> 00:30:53,320
they will themselves be exposed

451
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:58,560
and you won't have to do anything.

452
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:02,760
One day I was told

453
00:31:03,120 --> 00:31:05,360
that there is a servant, lady-servant

454
00:31:05,560 --> 00:31:09,240
who is a very possessed person, in the family.

455
00:31:09,480 --> 00:31:13,080
So I said "Get rid of her."

456
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:18,200
I went to the airport. On My way I stopped at that house

457
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:20,360
and the maid-servant just walked in, you see

458
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:23,560
and there was a big gutter flowing,

459
00:31:23,800 --> 00:31:26,880
I mean not a gutter but a open sort of a thing

460
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:31,360
and she saw Me and she fell in that.

461
00:31:32,360 --> 00:31:33,440
I said, "Oh God,"

462
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:36,200
so I told the driver to take the car a little ahead.

463
00:31:36,440 --> 00:31:40,800
And she fell in. It happens.

464
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:43,080
I was traveling by plane one day

465
00:31:43,320 --> 00:31:46,360
and the gentleman in front started just jumping.

466
00:31:46,880 --> 00:31:49,600
So a Sahaja Yogi asked, "Are you from TM?" He said, "How do you know?"

467
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:53,400
He said, "We know." So I sat back.

468
00:31:53,880 --> 00:31:57,120
It may be they may all have ...

469
00:31:57,680 --> 00:32:00,840
A day may come when they might start jumping like that.

470
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:04,960
Or a pilot might start jumping.

471
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:11,120
It's a big problem for Me.

472
00:32:16,360 --> 00:32:22,120
Even the lights ...

473
00:32:24,680 --> 00:32:26,320
... you enter into a church

474
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:29,680
and suddenly you find all the lights going off like this.

475
00:32:30,040 --> 00:32:33,760
Even in big banquets, I find, when I am sitting there

476
00:32:34,040 --> 00:32:35,480
and suddenly everybody comes and sit down

477
00:32:35,680 --> 00:32:37,840
and all their bhoots come around,

478
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:41,600
they start jumping and then people start looking, "What's happening,

479
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:44,680
is there a fire on?"

480
00:32:44,960 --> 00:32:45,680
So many things can happen,

481
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:49,440
like there was a gentleman very much possessed in a war

482
00:32:49,680 --> 00:32:51,280
and we were going to a ship

483
00:32:51,520 --> 00:32:55,760
and there was a little  platform on which we had to first jump

484
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:58,240
and the platform started doing like this, like that

485
00:32:58,440 --> 00:33:01,040
and the fellow didn't know what to do with it,

486
00:33:01,360 --> 00:33:04,960
he didn't understand why it was doing this.

487
00:33:05,920 --> 00:33:10,480
So when you reach that state you don't have to argue or do anything,

488
00:33:10,840 --> 00:33:13,640
even if you lift your eye

489
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:18,520
it happens that the person gets into problems.

490
00:33:18,880 --> 00:33:23,960
Or there could be some ego-oriented people, they'll melt down.

491
00:33:24,600 --> 00:33:27,120
First you have to do the drama of a guru,

492
00:33:27,360 --> 00:33:31,000
dress up in a way which is simple,

493
00:33:31,280 --> 00:33:34,760
you have to behave in a way which is very gentle,

494
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:36,280
because you have to attract them.

495
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:38,240
"Come along, come along, come along."

496
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:41,800
That's advertising, Advertising Department.

497
00:33:44,240 --> 00:33:48,360
And once it is done, that drama is done

498
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:52,800
it can be exposed very soon, if they will find out that you are not good,

499
00:33:53,040 --> 00:33:55,040
you are just a dramatist.

500
00:33:55,360 --> 00:33:58,400
Once the drama has been done then

501
00:33:58,720 --> 00:34:03,720
very cleverly you can bring out your real self before them.

502
00:34:04,200 --> 00:34:09,400
So first you don't show them that you are a real, hard taskmaster.

503
00:34:09,680 --> 00:34:11,320
Never.

504
00:34:11,560 --> 00:34:15,240
First use all your sweet qualities.

505
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:18,840
The more they are difficult the more I am gentle with them.

506
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:21,440
Then they come inside.

507
00:34:21,720 --> 00:34:25,560
Then you put to the mill and you can cure them.

508
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:29,480
First prepare them. First of all sometimes they are so frightened,

509
00:34:29,760 --> 00:34:34,280
